{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban default service charges and pre-set digital tip screens in hospitality",
        "additional_details": "In our view, the current tipping culture has become coercive and stressful as some restaurants routinely use \"drip pricing,\" adding a 12.5% charge at the end of a meal, forcing customers to awkwardly ask to remove it. We think digital payment screens with pre-set tipping suggestions use psychological pressure to guilt people into tipping for basic counter service. We think this creates a hostile environment and anxiety for consumers.",
        "background": "Prohibit hospitality businesses from automatically adding \"discretionary\" service charges to bills, and ban digital card readers from prompting customers with pre-set tip percentages before payment. We believe all tipping must be 100% voluntary and initiated by the customer.",
